      <block class="full_text">
        <p>LEAD: To the Editor:</p>
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The subway crisis would be greatly eased by adopting some elementary principles of business pricing: Increase the price of a token to $1.25, cutting the time needed to make change. Lower the cost of a 10-pack to $11, giving passengers added incentive to buy them and also reducing waiting time. The loss of revenue would be more than balanced by the rise in the price of individual tokens, a drop in fare evasion and an increase in ridership.</p>
        <p>LEO BOGART</p>
        <p>New York, June 27, 1990</p>
      </block>
